**Problem:** The app has no `express.json()` or `express.urlencoded()` middleware, and no validation on any inputs (query params, route params, request bodies). When POST/PUT/PATCH routes are added — as they inevitably will be — unvalidated input flows directly into business logic, enabling injection attacks.

**Recommendation:** Add body parsing and a validation layer now, before routes are extended.

